snippet.textDisplay:
I've seen a lot of people immediately whine and complain about it, with dumb things like "Why is it so big?", "It's basically an Xbox controller." and more stupid shortsighted crap like that. And if they would've read PlayStation's blog-post about it they'd probably use their brain for a bit. - But it took me all but about five minutes to start liking it. Cosmetically, it's a bit of a "shock", but I also like it; The two-tone with the major one being white, the blue detail that goes with PlayStation, the buttons all look nice, and I especially like the transparent ones making it look even classier. The design also makes me think of robots a lá 'Portal', 'The Talos Principle' and so on. - Other than that, besides the features and specifications they cram into this thing, the shape seems yet again nicer (it does remind me of the Xbox controller, at least the Razer Wolverine I have, which feels really nice). Also the two buttons next to the touchpad seem a little more ergonomically placed as well that they seem to stick out a little more. Because an immediate issue I had with those buttons and didn't go away is that it's difficult to find them by feel and difficult to press them down because you tend to hit the chassis of the controller, creating a huge delay (and miss) for captures for example.
Other than that, it looks great to me. Apart from the PS-logo, which looks like will still act as as button, I don't like that it's just the shape of the logo. They should've just kept it within a transparent round button, which this time around would've fit well with the other transparent buttons. But oh well... People are gonna love it and people who are complaining about the entire thing today will be eating their words.
